# CostTracking — Project Overview

A full-stack **personal expense & income tracking** app. Multi-user: each user logs in,
defines spending categories, records expenses (multi-item, multi-currency) and income, and
views analytics/reports of monthly spending.

The repo is a monorepo with two independent projects:

- `Frontend/` — Angular 21 SPA
- `Backend/` — Node.js + Express 5 REST API on MongoDB

---

## Backend (`Backend/`)

TypeScript + Express 5 + Mongoose (MongoDB). Runnable as a standalone server or serverless.

- **Entry**: `src/server.ts` (listens on `PORT`) → `src/app.ts` (Express app: cors, morgan,
  json, mounts router) → `src/serverless.ts` (serverless-http wrapper for deploy).
- **DB**: `src/config/db.config.ts` connects via `MONGO_URI`.
- **Routing**: `src/routes/app.routes.ts` mounts feature routers, then `routNotFound` +
  `errorHandler` from `src/handlers/exception.handler.ts`. API base paths:
  - `/api/auth` — register, login, refresh-token (`auth.routes.ts`)
  - `/api/exp` — expenses CRUD (`exp.routes.ts`)
  - `/api/cat` — categories CRUD (`category.routes.ts`)
  - `/api/income` — income CRUD (`income.routes.ts`)
- **Layers**: `routes/` → `controllers/` → `models/` (Mongoose schemas + data-access fns).
  - `middlewares/` — `auth.middleware.ts` (`authenticateToken` JWT guard),
    `validator.middlewares.ts` (`validateRequest`), `schemas.ts` (zod schemas).
  - `models/` — `user`, `exp` (expense w/ embedded `items[]`), `income`, `category`;
    plus `*.seed.ts` seed helpers. All domain data is scoped by `userId`.
  - `types/` — shared interfaces (`ResponseItem`, `ErrorWithStatus`, `TokenPayload`, etc.).
- **Auth**: JWT access token (1h) + refresh token (1d), passwords hashed with bcrypt in a
  `user.model` pre-save hook. Secrets from `SECRET_KEY` / `SECRET_KEY_REFRESH`.
- **Scripts**: `npm run dev` (tsx watch), `npm run build` (tsc), `npm run deploy` (serverless).

### Standard API response shape
Controllers return `{ message: string, data: T }` (`ResponseItem<T>`); errors flow through
`next(new ErrorWithStatus(msg, status))` to the central `errorHandler`.

---

## Frontend (`Frontend/`)

Angular 21 standalone app: zoneless change detection, signals, new control-flow syntax,
NgRx state, Tailwind v4, lucide-angular icons, ECharts (`ngx-echarts`) for charts.

- **Bootstrap**: `src/main.ts` → `src/app/app.ts` → `app.config.ts` (providers: router with
  view transitions, HttpClient + interceptors, app initializer, NgRx store/effects/devtools).
- **Routing** (`app.routes.ts`): lazy-loaded `auth` (guarded by `isLoggedOutGuard`) and
  `dashboard` (guarded by `isLoggedInGuard`); wildcard → `dashboard`.
  - `dashboard-routes.ts`: shell `Dashboard` component with children `category`, `expenses`
    (lazy `expenses.routes.ts`), `analytics` (reports), `income`; default → `analytics`.
- **Folders** under `src/app/`:
  - `auth/` — `login`, `register`, route guards.
  - `dashboard/` — feature areas: `layout/` (sidebar, header), `expenses/` (list, add, edit,
    details, filter), `income/`, `category/`, `analytics/` (reports, monthly-expenses).
  - `core/` — `services/` (auth, expenses, income, category HTTP services),
    `interceptors/` (auth, retry, auth-error), `guards/` (unsaved-changes), `interfaces/`,
    `app.utils.ts` (app initializer, token verify).
  - `common/` — reusable `components/` (expense-form, pagination, overlay) and `directives/`.
  - `store/` — NgRx slices for `expenses`, `income`, `category` (each: actions, reducer,
    effects, selectors). Root wiring in `store/app.store.ts` (`AppState`), plus
    `clear-state.metareducer.ts` which resets state on `logoutAction`.
- **Auth on the client**: `core/services/auth-service.ts` holds access/refresh tokens in
  signals, mirrors them to `localStorage` via effects, decodes the JWT for the current user,
  and drives login/logout/refresh. Interceptors attach the token and handle 401/refresh + retry.
- **Config**: API base URL in `src/environments/environment*.ts` (`API_URL`).
- **Scripts**: `npm run start` (ng serve), `npm run build` (prod), `npm test` (karma/jasmine).

---

## Conventions

- Backend domain queries are always filtered by `userId`; keep that constraint when adding endpoints.
- Frontend feature data flows through NgRx (actions → effects call `core/services` → reducers);
  prefer selectors over reading state directly in components.
- Each new domain entity typically needs: a Mongoose model + data-access fns, a controller, a
  router mounted in `app.routes.ts`, a zod schema, and a matching frontend service + store slice.
- Components are standalone; co-locate `*.ts`, template (`.html`), styles (`.scss`/`.css`), and `*.spec.ts`.
